London Lucy Knghtley
Sr. in answer to yd of 11: curitt relurne you thanckes for yd readiness in sending
forward of 5 reds, for which when you please you may draw the valew to my
most advantidge & when you finde an other penny worth of about £8:10
and £11„10 I would well have 5 reds more so assorted, which you may do att
good leasure and that some aurovers may do att good leasure and that come
bo by, for them I want most though not beeng in haste for either, you
please to provide them when best you can though itt should be 6 wee kes hence
& doubt I shall not be able to putt of yd kersies, so do not know what to do
with them, for the season goeth farr: & have a good quantitie of tykes on
hand, in case I could serve you with a bale for trjall, I shall send them you so
cheap, that I am confident, they came never cheaper, on which pleast to give
mee yd answer pr. first & so remaine with kindeselute
London pickering R robbeuson
S. 4is long sence I writt to you, whilst & did not thing butt, that by this time all
our goods, should have been sold, which I have not been able to do, pertely, because the
goods prove so bad, and pertelj because of the continuall french allarmes, which
is a most great hindraine to our trade, so that hetherto I have sold onely 12 cloathes
all the bayes & all the kersies, of which shall send you the acctt us. nent
I have not above ƒ200:- in cass for yd acctt, butt if the goods had been well, sure
they had been sold & great dealy of mony returned, butt now I can not butt them
off butt to such, as have no great know hedge of cloth so that I hope you will have
patience, as wellas 3 & besure that I do all possible endeavours to dispose of y toour
best: now have att least prevailed with our tyke makers that though yearne is
Dearer, yett have the tykds to former prijses, so in case you please to have a parcell
less mee have yd advise, for the goods that I have now & remade in a good
season &curiously assorted & send this day one bale forward to bruges which
cout. soo pe which & do for feare of forst, so they will be by m. Raphael coots
in case you please to have y send him yd order & lett mee know itt as also if
& can serve you with any more, before winter for C supose to have ready
1oo p more before the latter end of the nextmonth & so with kinde saluts
